### 4. Animation Strategy Summary

All animations use **framer-motion** (already installed at v12) and native `requestAnimationFrame`. No new dependencies needed.

| Element | Animation | Timing |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| Encouragement text | Fade in | 0.05s delay, 0.4s duration |
| Stat tile 1 (Posts) | Fade + slide up | 0.1s delay |
| Stat tile 2 (Words) | Fade + slide up | 0.18s delay |
| Stat tile 3 (Reactions) | Fade + slide up | 0.26s delay |
| Stat tile 4 (Views) | Fade + slide up | 0.34s delay |
| Counter animation (each tile) | Count from 0 to value | 800-1100ms, easeOutExpo |
| Best post card | Fade + slide up | 0.45s delay |
| Community highlights | Fade in | 0.55s delay |

The staggered reveal creates a reading-order flow: encouragement first, then stats left-to-right, then achievements, then social proof. This mirrors the psychological hierarchy: personal identity, personal metrics, personal achievement, social context.

